    "what_description": "\u00d7 Laeliocattleya welsiana is an intergeneric hybrid orchid belonging to the family Orchidaceae. It is a cross between Laelia and Cattleya, with a compact growth habit and relatively small size, typically reaching 12-18 inches in height. The plant produces a single, terminal inflorescence with 2-6 flowers, each measuring 3-4 inches in diameter, featuring a white or pale yellow lip and a yellow or greenish-yellow sepals and petals. The leaves are lanceolate to elliptic in shape, measuring 4-8 inches in length, and are dark green in color with a reddish-brown base. The flower and leaf characteristics of \u00d7 Laeliocattleya welsiana are influenced by its parents, with a mix of Laelia's compact growth and Cattleya's large, showy flowers.",
